• Stack: 1 server @ 8.8.8.8 running Nginx (web), app server, your code, MySQL.
• DNS: foobar.com with A record “www” -> 8.8.8.8.
• Web server role: serve static & reverse-proxy to app.
• App server role: run business logic.
• DB role: persist data (MySQL).
• Protocol: HTTP/TCP (or HTTPS if you terminate TLS).
Issues: single point of failure, deploy restarts cause downtime, no scale.
